news.title: Gujarat HC stays 15-day civil arrest of Rameshwar Developers' partner
news.para: While staying the civil custody of the builder, Rajesh Motiani, a partner in Rameshwar Developers, Justice A S Supehia said that there is no perversity in RERA’s order, but detaining the builder will not serve any purpose.

news.title: Century Plyboards lines up Rs 900 crore capex for capacity expansion
news.para: The company will be investing Rs 543 crore by the end of FY24 towards a greenfield MDF plant in Andhra Pradesh. The company has already invested Rs 57 crore in this plant, bringing the total investment to Rs 600 crore.

news.title: Haryana cabinet approves land pooling policy
news.para: The policy prescribed a timeline to be followed at various stages so the interests of land owners are protected and the objective of land development is achieved in a time-bound manner.

news.title: HSVP comes out with stringent policy for four-storey builder floors in Haryana
news.para: ​Now, an owner or occupant of residential plots wanting to raise four-storey structures will have to ensure that construction does not pose any kind of threat or damage to buildings, especially those sharing common walls.

news.title: Delhi government may soon bring proposal to hike circle rates by up to 30%
news.para: In a recent meeting to review the functioning of the revenue department, the lieutenant governor asked the divisional commissioner to make a detailed presentation on the “revision of circle rates” along with the reports of various working groups constituted for this purpose.

news.title: Farmhouses 'illegal', raze them in a week, Noida authority tells owners
news.para: The authority, in its notice dated July 27, rebutted the objections and also threatened to recover the cost of demolition if the farmhouse owners did not remove the structures in and around Sector 135 on their own.

news.title: Rajkummar Rao buys apartment in Mumbai's Juhu for Rs 44 crore
news.para: The transaction values the apartment spread over 3,456 sq ft at nearly Rs 1.27 lakh per sq ft pushing it into the tally of the country’s most expensive residential deals ever.

news.title: SC directs Supertech to share technical details with CBRI within one week
news.para: SC said information regarding the blast design, ground vibration, post demolition debris assessment, test blast and the vibration monitoring report shall be collated and supplied to CBRI by Supertech and Edifice Engineering within one week of the issuance of the communication.

news.title: CK Birla Group's arm HIL buys Fast Build Blocks for Rs 65 crore
news.para: Market sources said the deal structured as a business transfer agreement is for around Rs 65 crore and HIL will buy the entire manufacturing, distribution and sales network of autoclaved aerated concrete blocks and will take over the entire liabilities of the target company.

news.title: Dehradun civic body's online services not user-friendly, say residents
news.para: DMC started the online house tax payment facility in February 2021. Apart from public convenience, the move was aimed at reducing crowds at its office, especially in light of the pandemic.

news.title: PNB Housing's Rs 2,500 crore rights issue expected to be complete by Dec: Official
news.para: Following the rights issue, the shareholding of Punjab National Bank (PNB) as a promoter of the company would come down from the current level of 32.57 per cent to below 30 per cent.

news.title: DLF's net profit up 39% at Rs 469.57 crore in Q1 FY23
news.para: In a statement, DLF said its sales bookings jumped two-fold to Rs 2,040 crore during the April-June period of this fiscal year, compared with the year-ago period.

news.title: 315Work Avenue lease out 22,000 sq ft co-working space to MoEngage
news.para: 315Work Avenue currently manages around 30,000 seats spread over 1.5 million sq ft in Bengaluru, Mumbai and Pune. It plans to double its portfolio over a period of next one year.

news.title: Ludhiana: Vigilance books LIT ex-chief, five others for illegal sale of plots
news.para: Balasubramanium is a close aide of former cabinet minister Bharat Bhushan Ashu of the Congress. Sharma has been arrested in this case and further investigation is under progress.

news.title: Huda to auction 29 shops in Panchkula on August 3
news.para: Huda officials said according to the initial plan, NFS will be set up in 1.25 acre in Sector 5. In total, Huda is planning for 60 shops, but in the first phase, 29 shops will be auctioned.
